# Repo facts (docs/facts.md) — example

Copy to `docs/facts.md` in each repo (gitignore `docs/facts.md` if the repo is public and facts are sensitive).

## Repo identity

- **Repository**: `<name>`
- **Purpose**: one-line description

## Related Jira tasks

Internal scoping only — do not cite this file from RFCs, PRs, or code comments.

| Ticket | Relevance |
|--------|-----------|
| `CRM-NNNN` | Primary story for current work |

## Workspace path keys (machine-specific)

Usually defined in `~/.ai-playbook/facts.md`, not in public repos:

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `instructions_repo` | Clone path of this playbook (for Codex/Claude/Cursor `@` entrypoints) |
| `personal_projects_root` | Root directory for personal / pet-project repositories |
| `company_projects_root` | Root directory for company work repositories |

## Environment-specific keys (optional)

Used by shared skills when this repo defines overrides:

| Key | Value |
|-----|-------|
| `shared_docs_dir` | `~/Projects/.ai-playbook/` |
